parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Leaking fuel injectors can cause fuel leaks, engine misfires, and decreased engine performance, which can lead to accidents or engine damage.
Failure of the coolant pump can cause engine overheating, coolant leaks, and engine damage, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Leaking fuel rails can cause fuel leaks, engine misfires, and decreased engine performance, which can lead to accidents or engine damage.

The failure of the transmission sensor can cause the vehicle to lose power and acceleration, leading to unsafe conditions on the road, particularly on busy highways, and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle flashes a gearbox malfunction warning
the vehicle loses power and acceleration
the vehicle's electronics malfunction or shut down
the vehicle's power and acceleration are intermittent
